tspan.tspan: assume insert (write on current cell and move all chars after
head right one more cell, it's easy to implement) is a built-in
assume input string is in proper form, i.e. no leading zero is
allowed, and the input cannot be zero
process input string with functions in q2, so that an raw input
str will be initialized as # str A 1 B C _, where A, B, C are
indicate segments as #--, A--, B--, C--
#--: binary string, discard a digit for each its processing
A--: 2^m in 1s, where m is the exponent on that digit
B--: a helper string for doubling A--
C--: the 1s of every digit in binary string will be added here,
this string is the final result
